  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Honeycomb. A British home-cook's dish — the kind of recipe families adjust across generations. Adjustable for what you need."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Cookies bake fast and reward a chilled dough. Pull them out when the edges set and the middles still look slightly underdone."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What you need"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "ingredientsList",
        "attrs": {
          "defaultServings": 4,
          "items": [
            {
              "ingredientSlug": "granulated-sugar",
              "amount": 350,
              "unit": "g",
              "prepNote": "1 ¾ cup",
              "isOptional": false,
              "groupLabel": null
            },
            {
              "ingredientSlug": "golden-syrup",
              "amount": 160,
              "unit": "tbsp",
              "prepNote": "½ cup",
              "isOptional": false,
              "groupLabel": null
            },
            {
              "ingredientSlug": "water",
              "amount": 120,
              "unit": "ml",
              "prepNote": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "groupLabel": null
            },
            {
              "ingredientSlug": "sea-salt-fine",
              "amount": 0.5,
              "unit": "tsp",
              "prepNote": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "groupLabel": null
            },
            {
              "ingredientSlug": "bicarbonate-of-soda",
              "amount": 1,
              "unit": "tbsp",
              "prepNote": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "groupLabel": null
            },
            {
              "ingredientSlug": "dark-chocolate",
              "amount": 300,
              "unit": "g",
              "prepNote": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "groupLabel": null
            },
            {
              "ingredientSlug": "sea-salt-flakes",
              "amount": null,
              "unit": "g",
              "prepNote": "I use maldon sea salt flakes",
              "isOptional": false,
              "groupLabel": null
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Method"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Line a 9 inch square pan with parchment paper (sides and bottom). Set aside until needed."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Keep a spatula and a whisk ready, as you will need them towards the end of the cook time."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Place the sugar, golden syrup / corn syrup, water, and salt in a large saucepan (this mixture will expand a lot, so use a large pot with space)."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Gently stir to saturate the sugar with the water."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Heat over medium high heat, while swirling the pot frequently to ensure the sugar dissolves"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Brush the sides of the pot with a pastry brush dipped in cold water to dissolve the sugar crystals on the side of the pot. Do NOT stir the sugar syrup."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "When the sugar syrup comes to a boil and all the sugar has dissolved, clip a candy thermometer to the side of the pot."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Heat the sugar mixture until it reaches 300°F. Swirl the pot as you heat the sugar to make sure the syrup is evenly heating (check several spots in the syrup with the candy thermometer to make sure it's evenly heating)."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Get the prepared pan, whisk, and spatula ready when the sugar syrup is close to 300°F. You can use an oven mitt for whisking the sugar base in the following steps, if you like."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "When the sugar syrup reaches 300°F, remove the pot from the heat and immediately add all of the baking soda."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Whisk the baking soda well into the sugar syrup. Make sure to reach all the corners of the pot. The sugar syrup will expand into a foamy honeycomb mixture."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "As soon as the baking soda is thoroughly mixed in and the mixture has expanded, scrape the honeycomb mixture into the prepared pan."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Allow the mixture to harden for a few hours."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Once the candy is hardened, remove it from the pan and peel off the parchment paper. Place it on a cutting board."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Use the tip of a sharp knife to break the honeycomb into pieces."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Optionally - Dip the honeycomb toffee in tempered chocolate (you can dip them either fully or partially). Place them on a parchment paper lined tray and sprinkle salt on top before the chocolate sets."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Storing the toffee"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Uncoated honeycomb toffee – Store these honeycomb pieces in an air-tight container at room temperature for about 1 week (or 2 weeks if it's not humid). Place parchment paper or wax paper between layers of the honeycomb to prevent them from sticking to each other."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Chocolate coated honeycomb toffee – These can be stored at room temp for much longer (even up to a month) in an air-tight container."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Do NOT store these in the fridge or freezer."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "heading": "If something goes wrong",
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "symptom": "Mixture won't set",
              "cause": "Sugar didn't reach the right stage, or temperature was guessed.",
              "fix": "Use a sugar thermometer. Stages: soft-ball 115°C, hard-ball 125°C, soft-crack 135°C, hard-crack 150°C. Cold-water tests work but the thermometer doesn't lie."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "Sugar crystallised",
              "cause": "Mixture stirred after it started bubbling, or a stray crystal landed on the side of the pan.",
              "fix": "Don't stir once the sugar is dissolved. Brush the inside of the pan with a wet pastry brush to wash crystals down."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "Fudge is grainy",
              "cause": "Beaten too soon — while still too hot.",
              "fix": "Cool to 43°C before beating. The mixture turns from glossy to matte when ready to set."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "Mixture seized into a ball",
              "cause": "Water touched melted chocolate.",
              "fix": "Add a teaspoon of warm cream or water and stir until smooth — this is the trick. Drier seizing needs more liquid; thin seizing wants less."
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Variations"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Flavoured version: stir in a teaspoon of vanilla, almond, or peppermint extract once the mixture is off the heat."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Dip-coated: once set, dip pieces in melted dark chocolate and let drip on baking paper."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Best fresh. Leftovers keep two days in the fridge; reheat covered with a splash of liquid."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Where this dish lives"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A British home cook's dish. It sits among the recipes families remember without thinking about — the kind that gets adjusted across generations and never quite the same twice."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}